<item>
            <title>[MATH-782] BrentOptimizer: User-defined check block is badly placed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-782</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The CM implementation of Brent&apos;s original algorithm was supposed to allow for a user-defined stopping criterion (in addition to Brent&apos;s default one).&lt;br/&gt;
However, it turns out that this additional block of code is not at the right location, implying an unwanted early exit.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12552120">MATH-782</key>
            <summary>BrentOptimizer: User-defined check block is badly placed</summary>
